@title erl_tidy - a code cleaner for Erlang

@doc erl_tidy is a tool for cleaning up obsolete constructs in Erlang code.

Example: ```erl_tidy:dir("any-erlang-source-dir", [test, old_guard_tests]).'''
(the `test' option assures that no files are modified).

See the {@link erl_tidy} module for more details.
